odeling methodology that categorizes threats into Spoofing, Tampering, Repudiation, Information Disclosure, Denial of Service, and Elevation of Privilege."},{"name":"ICS-specific threat models","description":"Custom threat models tailored for Industrial Control Systems, considering operational technology (OT) constraints and real-time requirements."}],"tools":[{"name":"Microsoft Threat Modeling Tool","purpose":"Facilitates STRIDE-based threat modeling for identifying and mitigating security issues during design."},{"name":"NIST 800-30 (Adapted for ICS)","purpose":"Provides a framework for risk assessment, adapted to address ICS-specific threats and vulnerabilities."}],"case_study":{"example":"A power plant DCS underwent a security assessment using STRIDE, identifying critical tampering risks in firmware updates. Mitigations included secure boot and cryptographic verification."}},"audit_and_compliance_verification":{"why":"To verify adherence to secure-by-design principles and track closure of security-related issues.","audit_checklist":["Verify documented evidence of threat modeling for the product/patch.","Confirm all identified security issues have been addressed or have approved exceptions.","Check traceability of security requirements to design and testing phases."],"metrics":[{"kpi":"Percentage of security issues resolved before release","target":"100%"},{"kpi":"Number of critical vulnerabilities post-release","target":"0"}],"compliance_procedure":"Documentation must include threat models, issue tracking logs, and verification reports. Reviews are conducted by the security team before release approval."},"training_and_competency_requirements":{"why":"To ensure personnel are capable of identifying and addressing security issues in ICS products.","training_programs":[{"name":"ISA/IEC 62443 Cybersecurity Certifications","description":"Covers secure development practices for ICS, including secure-by-design principles."},{"name":"GICSP (Global Industrial Cyber Security Professional)","description":"Provides foundational knowledge of ICS security, including risk assessment and mitigation."}],"competency_assessment":"Annual reviews of engineering staff’s proficiency in threat modeling and secure design, including practical evaluations."},"tooling_and_automation_support":{"why":"To integrate security checks into the development lifecycle efficiently.","tools":[{"name":"Static Application Security Testing (SAST) tools","purpose":"Automatically identify vulnerabilities in source code during development."},{"name":"ICS-specific vulnerability scanners","purpose":"Scan for known vulnerabilities in ICS components (e.g., PLCs, RTUs)."}],"automation_strategy":"Integrate SAST and vulnerability scanners into CI/CD pipelines, with gated releases based on security issue resolution."},"handling_legacy_systems_and_constraints":{"why":"Legacy ICS components may not support modern security standards, requiring compensatory measures.","strategies":[{"approach":"Network segmentation","description":"Isolate legacy systems in separate zones to limit exposure to threats."},{"approach":"Compensating controls","description":"Implement additional monitoring (e.g., IDS/IPS) to detect and respond to anomalies."}],"example_policy":"Legacy systems must undergo a risk assessment, and compensating controls must be documented in the security design document."},"stakeholder_collaboration_and_governance":{"why":"Alignment between engineering, security, and management is critical for enforcing secure-by-design principles.","governance_model":{"name":"RACI Matrix for SM-11","roles":[{"role":"Security Team","responsibility":"Accountable for threat modeling and issue validation."},{"role":"Engineering Team","responsibility":"Responsible for implementing fixes for security issues."},{"role":"Management","responsibility":"Consulted for release approvals and resource allocation."}]},"conflict_resolution":"Disputes over issue severity or mitigation are escalated to a cr