m before release."},"training_and_competency_requirements":{"why":"To ensure personnel are competent in identifying and addressing security-related issues.","training_programs":[{"name":"ISA/IEC 62443 Cybersecurity Certifications","description":"Certifications covering ICS security standards and best practices."},{"name":"GICSP (Global Industrial Cyber Security Professional)","description":"Training focused on securing industrial control systems."}],"competency_assessment":"Annual reviews of personnel competency in security validation and verification processes, including practical assessments."},"tooling_and_automation_support":{"why":"To automate and streamline the verification and validation of security-related issues.","tools":[{"name":"Static Application Security Testing (SAST) tools","purpose":"To identify vulnerabilities in code before release."},{"name":"Dynamic Application Security Testing (DAST) tools","purpose":"To test running applications for security vulnerabilities."}],"automation_strategy":"Integrate SAST and DAST tools into the CI/CD pipeline to automatically scan for and report security issues during development and before release."},"handling_legacy_systems_and_constraints":{"why":"Legacy systems may not support modern security validation tools and processes.","strategies":[{"approach":"Network segmentation","description":"Isolate legacy systems to reduce exposure to potential threats."},{"approach":"Compensating controls","description":"Implement additional security measures such as intrusion detection systems to monitor legacy systems."}],"example_policy":"A policy outlining the use of compensating controls and enhanced monitoring for legacy systems that cannot meet modern security validation requirements."},"stakeholder_collaboration_and_governance":{"why":"Effective collaboration between engineering, security, and management is essential for addressing security-related issues.","governance_model":{"name":"RACI Matrix","roles":[{"role":"Securit