/en/work/solutions/cybersecurity/","description":"Schneider’s reference architectures for boundary control testing."}]},{"id":"KA3","title":"Dynamic Boundary Management","description":"Procedures to update trust boundaries during system modifications (e.g., cloud migration). Critical for maintaining SR-2(b) compliance in evolving ICS environments.","related_links":[{"title":"Microsoft Azure IoT Edge Security","url":"https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/iot-edge/iot-edge-security-management","description":"Microsoft’s approach to managing trust boundaries in hybrid ICS/cloud setups."},{"title":"AWS Industrial IoT Security Best Practices","url":"https://aws.amazon.com/iot-core/industrial-iot/security/","description":"AWS guidelines for dynamic trust boundaries in IIoT."}]},{"id":"KA4","title":"Boundary-Specific Threat Scenarios","description":"Development of attack scenarios targeting each trust boundary (e.g., MITM at IT/OT interfaces). Supports SR-2(b) by contextualizing threats to boundary vulnerabilities.","related_links":[{"title":"Dragos ICS Threat Assessment Framework","url":"https://www.dragos.com/resource/dragos-threat-assessment-framework/","description":"Dragos’ methodology for boundary-focused ICS threat modeling."},{"title":"MITRE ATT&CK for ICS","url":"https://attack.mitre.org/matrices/ics/","description":"Tactics for exploiting trust boundaries in ICS (e.g., T0816)."}]}],"name":"Threat model","description":"A process shall be employed to ensure that all products shall have a threat model specific to the current development scope of the product with the following characteristics (where applicable): b) trust boundaries;","details":{"risk_assessment_and_threat_modeling":{"why":"Identifying trust boundaries is critical to understanding where security controls must be enforced to prevent unauthorized access or data leakage.","methodologies":[{"name":"STRIDE","description":"A threat modeling methodology that categorizes threats into Spoofing, Tampering, Re