    {"practice":"3","code":"SD-4","subCode":"f) all trust boundaries are documented as part of the design; and","explanation":"Documenting trust boundaries ensures that security controls are applied at critical interfaces between trusted and untrusted zones, reducing attack surfaces in ICS environments.","context":"Trust boundaries define where security measures must be enforced, such as between OT and IT networks or between different security zones in an industrial control system.","challenges":["Identifying all trust boundaries in complex ICS architectures with legacy systems. Example: A power plant with mixed vendor PLCs may have undocumented communication paths.","Maintaining boundary documentation during system updates. Example: A firmware upgrade on a RTU may introduce new network interfaces.","Ensuring consistency between physical and logical boundaries. Example: A firewall rule may conflict with a VLAN segmentation policy.","Managing boundaries in multi-tenant industrial clouds. Example: Shared SCADA systems in cloud-based IIoT platforms.","Validating boundary documentation against actual traffic flows. Example: Unauthorized MODBUS traffic crossing zone boundaries."],"best_practices":[{"description":"Use network segmentation diagrams to visualize trust boundaries. Example: Siemens' Industrial Security Configuration Manual provides templates for zone/conduit diagrams.","url":" https://cache.industry.siemens.com/dl/files/109/109738/10973833/industrial_security_manual_en.pdf","url_description":"Siemens' guide for documenting security zones in industrial networks (Section 4.2)"},{"description":"Implement automated boundary validation tools. Example: Rockwell's FactoryTalk AssetCentre can monitor and alert on boundary violations.","url":" https://literature.rockwellautomation.com/idc/groups/literature/documents/at/fact-um001_-en-p.pdf","url_description":"Rockwell's guide to boundary monitoring with FactoryTalk (Chapter 7)"},{"description":"Conduct regular boundary audits using packet captures. Example: Wireshark industrial protocol filters can detect unauthorized cross-boundary traffic.","url":" https://www.honeywellprocess.com/library/support/Public/Documents/cybersecurity-best-practices-guide.pdf","url_description":"Honeywell's ICS boundary monitoring techniques (Page 23)"},{"description":"Integrate boundary documentation with change management systems. Example: Schneider Electric's EcoStruxure tracks boundary changes across versions.","url":"https://www.se.com/ww/en/work/support/cybersecurity/guidelines.jsp","url_description":"Schneider's boundary change management guidelines"}],"key_aspects":[{"id":"KA1","title":"Boundary Identification Methodology","description":"Systematic approach to identify all trust boundaries through asset inventory, data flow analysis, and threat modeling. Critical for IEC 62443-4-1 compliance as it forms the foundation for zone segmentation.","related_links":[{"title":"ISA-99 Boundary Identification Guide","url":"https://www.isa.org/standards-and-publications/isa-standards/isa-99-standards","description":"ISA's methodology for identifying ICS trust boundaries"},{"title":"Cisco Industrial IoT Boundary Best Practices","url":" https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/solutions/industries/manufacturing/industrial-iot-security.html","description":"Cisco's approach to IIoT boundary documentation"}]},{"id":"KA2","title":"Boundary Documentation Standards","description":"Standardized templates for recording boundary attributes (protocols, assets, security controls) ensuring consistency across projects. Aligns with SD-4(f) requirements for maintainable documentation.","related_links":[{"title":"NIST SP 800-82 Rev3 ICS Documentation","url":"https://nvlpubs.nist.gov/nistpubs/SpecialPublications/NIST.SP.800-82r3.pdf","description":"NIST guidelines for ICS boundary documentation (Section 6.2)"},{"title":"ABB Industrial Security Documentation Framework","url":" https://new.abb.com/docs/librariesprovider37/default-docume