ing industrial control systems."}],"competency_assessment":"Annual reviews of personnel competency in threat analysis and security issue resolution."},"tooling_and_automation_support":{"why":"Automation and tools streamline the investigation and documentation of security issues.","tools":[{"name":"SIEM (Security Information and Event Management)","purpose":"Aggregates and analyzes security alerts for threat detection."},{"name":"JIRA with Security Plugins","purpose":"Tracks and manages security-related issues with workflow automation."}],"automation_strategy":"Integrate SIEM alerts with issue tracking tools to automate initial threat categorization and assignment."},"handling_legacy_systems_and_constraints":{"why":"Legacy ICS components may lack modern security features, requiring alternative approaches.","strategies":[{"approach":"Network Segmentation","description":"Isolate legacy systems to limit exposure to threats."},{"approach":"Compensating Controls","description":"Implement additional monitoring and access controls for legacy systems."}],"example_policy":"Legacy systems must undergo a compensating controls review before integration into the network."},"stakeholder_collaboration_and_governance":{"why":"Effective collaboration between security, engineering, and management ensures comprehensive threat analysis.","governance_model":{"name":"RACI Matrix for Security Issue Review","roles":[{"role":"Security Team","responsibility":"Lead threat analysis and issue resolution."},{"role":"Engineering Team","responsibility":"Provide technical details and implement fixes."},{"role":"Management","responsibility":"Approve resource allocation and policy changes."}]},"conflict_resolution":"A mediation process involving senior management resolves conflicts between security and engineering priorities."},"continuous_improvement_and_updates":{"why":"Updating practices based on new threats and lessons learned ensures ongoing security.","update_process":[{"step":"Monitor Threat In