age security issues and remediation plans within a DevSecOps pipeline."},{"name":"Tenable.io","purpose":"Automate vulnerability scanning and prioritize remediation efforts based on risk."}],"automation_strategy":"Integrate automated vulnerability scanning and issue tracking tools into the CI/CD pipeline to ensure security issues are identified and remediated early in the development process."},"handling_legacy_systems_and_constraints":{"why":"Legacy ICS components often cannot meet modern security standards, requiring alternative approaches to remediation.","strategies":[{"approach":"Network Segmentation","description":"Isolate legacy systems in secure network zones to limit exposure to threats."},{"approach":"Compensating Controls","description":"Implement additional security measures (e.g., intrusion detection systems) to mitigate risks in legacy systems."}],"example_policy":"A policy for legacy PLCs mandates network segmentation, regular vulnerability assessments, and the use of compensating controls if patches cannot be applied."},"stakeholder_collaboration_and_governance":{"why":"Effective remediation requires collaboration between engineering, security, and management teams.","governance_model":{"name":"RACI Matrix for ICS Security","roles":[{"role":"Security Team","responsibility":"Identify and assess security issues."},{"role":"Engineering Team","responsibility":"Develop and implement remediation plans."},{"role":"Management","responsibility":"Approve residual risk levels and resource allocation."}]},"conflict_resolution":"A documented escalation process for resolving conflicts between engineering and security priorities, including risk-based decision-making frameworks."},"continuous_improvement_and_updates":{"why":"To adapt remediation processes based on new threats and lessons learned.","update_process":[{"step":"Monitor Threat Intelligence","description":"Regularly review CISA alerts and ICS-CERT advisories for new vulnerabilities."},{"step":"Review Incid