n and Event Management)","purpose":"Monitors compensating controls for deferred issues."}],"automation_strategy":"Integrate issue tracking tools with DevSecOps pipelines to flag deferred issues automatically."},"handling_legacy_systems_and_constraints":{"why":"Legacy systems often require deferred security updates due to compatibility issues.","strategies":[{"approach":"Network Segmentation","description":"Isolate legacy systems to reduce the risk of deferred vulnerabilities."},{"approach":"Compensating Controls","description":"Implement additional security measures to mitigate risks until issues are resolved."}],"example_policy":"Legacy systems with deferred security updates must be documented, risk-assessed, and isolated within a segmented network zone."},"stakeholder_collaboration_and_governance":{"why":"Effective governance ensures that deferred issues are managed collaboratively.","governance_model":{"name":"RACI Matrix","roles":[{"role":"Security Team","responsibility":"Assess and document risks of deferred issues."},{"role":"Engineering Team","responsibility":"Implement compensating controls for deferred issues."},{"role":"Management","responsibility":"Approve deferral decisions and monitor resolution timelines."}]},"conflict_resolution":"A governance committee reviews and resolves conflicts between engineering and security priorities."},"continuous_improvement_and_updates":{"why":"To incorporate new threat intelligence and lessons learned into the deferral process.","update_process":[{"step":"Review CISA Alerts","description":"Regularly check for new ICS vulnerabilities that may affect deferred issues."},{"step":"Quarterly Risk Register Review","description":"Reassess deferred issues and update risk assessments as needed."}],"lessons_learned":"Incidents related to deferred issues are analyzed and used to refine deferral policies."}},"standard_compliance":"IEC 62443-4-1","last_updated":"2023-10-15"} 
