enial of Service, Elevation of Privilege) that security updates must mitigate."},{"name":"ICS-specific threat models","description":"Focuses on operational technology (OT) environments to identify unique threats to ICS components."}],"tools":[{"name":"Microsoft Threat Modeling Tool","purpose":"Assists in creating threat models to identify vulnerabilities addressed by security updates."},{"name":"NIST 800-30 adapted for SCADA systems","purpose":"Provides a framework for risk assessment tailored to ICS environments."}],"case_study":{"example":"A power plant's DCS received a security update for a vulnerability identified via STRIDE analysis. Documentation included affected version numbers and mitigation steps."}},"audit_and_compliance_verification":{"why":"To verify that security update documentation meets IEC 62443-4-1 requirements.","audit_checklist":["Check if documentation includes affected product version numbers.","Verify that update release notes detail vulnerabilities addressed.","Confirm documentation is accessible to users."],"metrics":[{"kpi":"Percentage of security updates with complete documentation","target":"100%"},{"kpi":"Time to publish documentation after update release","target":"≤ 7 days"}],"compliance_procedure":"Review documentation against SUM-2 requirements during internal audits and before release."},"training_and_competency_requirements":{"why":"To ensure personnel understand how to document security updates properly.","training_programs":[{"name":"ISA/IEC 62443 Cybersecurity Certifications","description":"Covers secure development and maintenance practices, including documentation."},{"name":"GICSP","description":"Provides ICS-specific security training, including update management."}],"competency_assessment":"Annual reviews of documentation quality and adherence to SUM-2."},"tooling_and_automation_support":{"why":"To automate documentation generation and ensure consistency.","tools":[{"name":"GitHub Security Advisories","purpose":"Automates 