ited to: b) instructions on how to apply approved patches manually and via an automated process;","details":{"risk_assessment_and_threat_modeling":{"why":"To ensure that security patches address relevant threats and vulnerabilities in the ICS environment.","methodologies":[{"name":"STRIDE","description":"Used to identify potential threats (Spoofing, Tampering, Repudiation, Information Disclosure, Denial of Service, Elevation of Privilege) that patches may mitigate."},{"name":"ICS-specific threat models","description":"Focuses on operational technology (OT) threats, such as unauthorized access to PLCs or disruption of control loops."}],"tools":[{"name":"Microsoft Threat Modeling Tool","purpose":"To model and document threats relevant to ICS components receiving patches."},{"name":"NIST 800-30 (Adapted for ICS)","purpose":"To assess risks associated with unpatched vulnerabilities in ICS environments."}],"case_study":{"example":"A power plant used STRIDE to prioritize patches for its DCS, focusing on Tampering and Denial of Service threats. Automated patch deployment reduced exposure to critical vulnerabilities by 70%."}},"audit_and_compliance_verification":{"why":"To verify that patch documentation and deployment processes comply with IEC 62443-4-1 requirements.","audit_checklist":["Verify that patch documentation includes manual and automated deployment instructions.","Check that patch deployment records are maintained for audit purposes.","Confirm that patch testing procedures are documented and followed."],"metrics":[{"kpi":"Percentage of patches with documented deployment instructions","target":"100%"},{"kpi":"Time to deploy critical patches","target":"≤7 days from release"}],"compliance_procedure":"Documentation reviews and patch deployment logs are audited quarterly. Evidence includes signed-off patch records and user acknowledgments of documentation."},"training_and_competency_requirements":{"why":"To ensure personnel understand patch documentation and deployment processes.","training_programs":[{"name":"ISA/IEC 62443 Cybersecurity Certifications","description":"Covers secure patch management in ICS environments."},{"name":"GICSP","description":"Global Industrial Cyber Security Professional training includes ICS patch management modules."}],"competency_assessment":"Annual reviews of staff competency in patch deployment, including hands-on tests for manual and automated processes."},"tooling_and_automation_support":{"why":"To streamline patch documentation and deployment in compliance with SUM-2.","tools":[{"name":"WSUS (Windows Server Update Services)","purpose":"Automates patch deployment for Windows-based ICS components."},{"name":"Ansible","purpose":"Orchestrates patch deployment across heterogeneous ICS devices."}],"automation_strategy":"Integrate patch tools with CI/CD pipelines to validate patches in a test environment before automated deployment to production."},"handling_legacy_systems_and_constraints":{"why":"Legacy ICS devices may not support automated patching.","strategies":[{"approach":"Network segmentation","description":"Isolate legacy systems to reduce attack surface while manual patches are applied."},{"approach":"Virtual patching","description":"Use IPS/IDS to mitigate vulnerabilities until patches can be deployed."}],"example_policy":"Legacy systems must be documented in a registry with compensating controls (e.g., network segmentation) if automated patching is unsupported."},"stakeholder_collaboration_and_governance":{"why":"Patch management requires coordination between OT, IT, and security teams.","governance_model":{"name":"RACI Matrix for Patch Management","roles":[{"role":"OT Engineers","responsibility":"Test and approve patches for ICS compatibility."},{"role":"Security Team","responsibility":"Prioritize patches based on risk assessments."}]},"conflict_resolution":"A cross-functional Change Advisory Board (CAB) resolves disputes, balancing security and operational priorities."},"continuous_improv