tion":"Case study on patch testing in critical infrastructure."}]},{"id":"KA3","title":"Vendor Coordination","description":"Structured collaboration with vendors to ensure timely and reliable patch delivery for proprietary ICS components.","related_links":[{"title":"Siemens ICS Vulnerability Handling","url":"https://www.siemens.com/global/en/products/services/cert.html","description":"Siemens' process for vulnerability disclosure and patching."},{"title":"ABB Security Advisory Process","url":"https://new.abb.com/about/technology/cyber-security","description":"ABB's approach to coordinating patches with customers."}]},{"id":"KA4","title":"Regulatory Compliance","description":"Alignment of patch management processes with industry-specific regulations to avoid compliance violations.","related_links":[{"title":"NERC CIP Patch Management Requirements","url":"https://www.nerc.com/pa/Stand/Pages/CIPStandards.aspx","description":"NERC's standards for patch management in power grids."},{"title":"FDA Guidance on Medical Device Patching","url":" https://www.fda.gov/medical-devices/digital-health-center-excellence/cybersecurity","description":"FDA's guidelines for patching medical ICS devices."}]}],"name":"Timely delivery of security patches","description":"A process shall be employed to define a policy that specifies the timeframes for delivering and qualifying security updates to product users and to ensure that this policy is followed. At a minimum, this policy shall consider the following factors: a) The potential impact of the vulnerability;","details":{"risk_assessment_and_threat_modeling":{"why":"To prioritize patches based on the severity of vulnerabilities and their potential impact on ICS operations.","methodologies":[{"name":"STRIDE","description":"Used to classify threats and assess the impact of vulnerabilities in ICS components."},{"name":"DREAD","description":"Helps in quantifying the risk associated with vulnerabilities to prioritize patching."}],"tools":[{"name