    {"practice":"8","code":"SG-2","subCode":"undefined","explanation":"The requirement mandates documenting security measures expected from the external environment to ensure defense in depth for industrial control systems (ICS).","context":"This practice ensures that product documentation clearly outlines security dependencies on the external environment, aiding in risk assessment and mitigation.","challenges":["Identifying all environmental dependencies: Complex ICS environments may have undocumented dependencies. Example: A PLC may rely on network segmentation not documented by the vendor.","Ensuring documentation accuracy: Outdated or incomplete documentation can mislead security assessments. Example: A legacy HMI system's documentation may not reflect current network configurations.","Aligning with organizational policies: External measures must comply with internal security policies. Example: A vendor's recommended firewall rules may conflict with corporate IT policies.","Managing third-party risks: External environments often involve third-party components. Example: A cloud-based SCADA system may depend on a CSP's security measures.","Maintaining documentation updates: Security measures evolve, requiring regular updates. Example: A patch management system's documentation may not reflect new vulnerabilities."],"best_practices":[{"description":"Conduct a thorough security assessment of the external environment to identify all dependencies. Example: Use network mapping tools to document all connected devices and their security postures.","url":" https://www.siemens.com/global/en/products/automation/industry-software/automation-software/pcs7/security.html","url_description":"Siemens' guide on securing PCS 7 environments, relevant for documenting external dependencies."},{"description":"Collaborate with vendors to ensure documentation aligns with actual security measures. Example: Jointly review firewall configurations with the vendor to validate documentation.","url":" https://www.honeywellprocess.com/library/support/technical-documents/Pages/cybersecurity.aspx","url_description":"Honeywell's technical documents on cybersecurity, useful for validating vendor-provided security measures."},{"description":"Implement a version control system for security documentation to track changes. Example: Use Git to manage updates to firewall rule documentation.","url":"https://www.rockwellautomation.com/en-us/support/security.html","url_description":"Rockwell Automation's security support page, offering tools for documentation management."},{"description":"Regularly audit external security measures to ensure compliance with documentation. Example: Perform quarterly reviews of network segmentation against documented policies.","url":"https://www.schneider-electric.com/en/work/support/cybersecurity/","url_description":"Schneider Electric's cybersecurity support, including audit guidelines for external measures."}],"key_aspects":[{"id":"KA1","title":"Environmental Security Dependencies","description":"Document all security measures provided by the external environment, such as network segmentation, firewalls, and intrusion detection systems. This ensures clarity on security responsibilities and aids in risk assessment.","related_links":[{"title":"Cisco Industrial IoT Security Guide","url":" https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/solutions/industries/manufacturing/industrial-iot-security-guide.html","description":"Cisco's guide on securing industrial IoT environments, relevant for documenting dependencies."},{"title":"ISA/IEC 62443 Cybersecurity Standards","url":" https://www.isa.org/standards-and-publications/isa-standards/isa-iec-62443-series-of-standards","description":"ISA's standards for industrial cybersecurity, providing a framework for documenting security measures."}]},{"id":"KA2","title":"Vendor Collaboration","description":"Engage with vendors to validate and update security documentation. This ensures alignment between documented measures and actual implementations.","related_links":[{"title":"Honeywell Process Solutions Cybersecurity","url":" https://www.honeywellprocess.com/library/support/technical-documents/Pages/cybersecurity.aspx","description":"Honeywell's technical documents on cybersecurity, useful for vendor collaboration."},{"title":"Siemens PCS 7 Security","url":" https://www.siemens.com/global/en/products/automation/industry-software/automation-software/pcs7/security.html","description":"Siemens' guide on securing PCS 7 environments, relevant for vendor collaboration."}]},{"id":"KA3","title":"Documentation Version Control","description":"Implement version control for security documentation to track changes and ensure consistency. This aids in maintaining up-to-date and accurate records.","related_links":[{"title":"Rockwell Automation Security Support","url":"https://www.rockwellautomation.com/en-us/support/security.html","description":"Rockwell Automation's security support page, offering tools for documentation management."},{"title":"Git for Documentation Management","url":"https://git-scm.com/doc","description":"Git's official documentation, useful for implementing version control."}]},{"id":"KA4","title":"Regular Audits","description":"Conduct regular audits of external security measures to ensure compliance with documented policies. This helps identify and address discrepancies promptly.","related_links":[{"title":"Schneider Electric Cybersecurity Support","url":"https://www.schneider-electric.com/en/work/support/cybersecurity/","description":"Schneider Electric's cybersecurity support, including audit guidelines."},{"title":"NIST SP 800-82 Guide to ICS Security","url":"https://csrc.nist.gov/publications/detail/sp/800-82/rev-2/final","description":"NIST's guide to ICS security, providing audit best practices."}]}],"name":"Defense in depth measures expected in the environment","description":"A process shall be employed to create product user documentation that describes the security defense in depth measures expected to be provided by the external environment in which the product is to be used.","details":{"risk_assessment_and_threat_modeling":{"why":"To ensure that defense in depth measures are appropriately documented and aligned with the threat landscape.","methodologies":[{"name":"STRIDE","description":"Used to identify potential threats (Spoofing, Tampering, Repudiation, Information Disclosure, Denial of Service, Elevation of Privilege) in the environment."},{"name":"ICS-specific threat models","description":"Tailored threat modeling approaches for Industrial Control Systems to address unique operational technology (OT) risks."}],"tools":[{"name":"Microsoft Threat Modeling Tool","purpose":"Facilitates STRIDE-based threat modeling for documenting security measures."},{"name":"NIST 800-30 adapted for SCADA","purpose":"Provides a framework for risk assessment in ICS environments."}],"case_study":{"example":"A power plant documented defense in depth measures for its DCS (Distributed Control System), including network segmentation, firewalls, and intrusion detection systems, aligned with IEC 62443-4-1."}},"audit_and_compliance_verification":{"why":"To verify that defense in depth measures are documented and implemented as per IEC 62443-4-1 requirements.","audit_checklist":["Verify that product user documentation includes defense in depth measures.","Check alignment of documented measures with actual environment configurations.","Review evidence of risk assessments supporting the documented measures."],"metrics":[{"kpi":"Percentage of documented defense in depth measures implemented","target":"100%"},{"kpi":"Number of gaps identified during audit","target":"0"}],"compliance_procedure":"Documentation must be reviewed annually and updated based on changes in the threat landscape or environment."},"training_and_competency_requirements":{"why":"To ensure personnel understand and can document defense in depth measures effectively.","training_programs":[{"name":"ISA/IEC 62443 Cybersecurity Fundamentals Specialist","description":"Covers foundational knowledge on ICS security, including defense in depth."},{"name":"GICSP (Global Industrial Cyber Security Professional)","description":"Provides training on securing ICS environments, including documentation practices."}],"competency_assessment":"Annual reviews of personnel competency in documenting and implementing defense in depth measures."},"tooling_and_automation_support":{"why":"To streamline the documentation and verification of defense in depth measures.","tools":[{"name":"SIEM (Security Information and Event Management)","purpose":"Monitors and logs security events to validate defense in depth measures."},{"name":"GRC (Governance, Risk, and Compliance) platforms","purpose":"Automates compliance tracking and documentation management."}],"automation_strategy":"Integrate documentation tools with DevSecOps pipelines to ensure continuous compliance and updates."},"handling_legacy_systems_and_constraints":{"why":"Legacy systems may not support modern defense in depth measures, requiring compensating controls.","strategies":[{"approach":"Network segmentation","description":"Isolate legacy systems to limit exposure to threats."},{"approach":"Compensating controls","description":"Implement additional monitoring and access controls to mitigate risks."}],"example_policy":"A policy for legacy PLCs mandates network segmentation and regular vulnerability assessments as compensating controls."},"stakeholder_collaboration_and_governance":{"why":"Effective documentation of defense in depth measures requires collaboration across teams.","governance_model":{"name":"RACI Matrix for SG-2","roles":[{"role":"Security Team","responsibility":"Define and document defense in depth measures."},{"role":"Engineering Team","responsibility":"Implement and validate measures in the environment."},{"role":"Management","responsibility":"Approve and oversee compliance with documentation requirements."}]},"conflict_resolution":"A cross-functional committee reviews and resolves conflicts between security and operational priorities."},"continuous_improvement_and_updates":{"why":"Defense in depth measures must evolve with emerging threats and technologies.","update_process":[{"step":"Monitor threat intelligence","description":"Regularly review CISA alerts and ICS-CERT advisories for new vulnerabilities."},{"step":"Review and update documentation","description":"Update defense in depth measures based on new threats or changes in the environment."}],"lessons_learned":"Incorporate findings from security incidents or audits into updated documentation and policies."}},"standard_compliance":"IEC 62443-4-1","last_updated":"2023-10-25"} 
