yber Security Professional)","description":"Certification focused on securing industrial control systems."}],"competency_assessment":"Annual reviews of personnel competency, including practical assessments of their ability to apply hardening guidelines."},"tooling_and_automation_support":{"why":"To streamline the implementation and maintenance of the defense in depth strategy.","tools":[{"name":"SIEM (Security Information and Event Management)","purpose":"To monitor and analyze security events across the ICS network."},{"name":"Vulnerability scanners (e.g., Nessus, Qualys)","purpose":"To identify and remediate vulnerabilities in ICS components."}],"automation_strategy":"Integration of vulnerability scanning and patch management tools into the DevSecOps pipeline to ensure continuous compliance with hardening guidelines."},"handling_legacy_systems_and_constraints":{"why":"Legacy systems may not support modern security standards, requiring alternative strategies.","strategies":[{"approach":"Network segmentation","description":"Isolate legacy systems in separate network segments to limit exposure to threats."},{"approach":"Compensating controls","description":"Implement additional controls (e.g., intrusion detection systems) to mitigate risks from legacy systems."}],"example_policy":"A policy for legacy system integration mandates network segmentation and regular vulnerability assessments for all legacy ICS components."},"stakeholder_collaboration_and_governance":{"why":"Effective collaboration between engineering, security, and management teams is essential for implementing the defense in depth strategy.","governance_model":{"name":"RACI Matrix for ICS Security","roles":[{"role":"Security Team","responsibility":"Define and enforce hardening guidelines."},{"role":"Engineering Team","responsibility":"Implement hardening guidelines in product design and deployment."},{"role":"Management","responsibility":"Allocate resources and oversee compliance."}]},"conflict_resolution":"A formal escalation process is used to resolve conflicts between engineering and security priorities, with final decisions made by the governance committee."},"continuous_improvement_and_updates":{"why":"To adapt the defense in depth strategy based on new threats and lessons learned.","update_process":[{"step":"Monitor threat intelligence","description":"Regularly review CISA alerts and other sources for new ICS vulnerabilities."},{"step":"Review audit findings","description":"Incorporate findings from compliance audits into the hardening guidelines."}],"lessons_learned":"After a phishing attack bypassed initial defenses, multi-factor authentication (MFA) was added to the defense in depth strategy for all remote access points."}},"standard_compliance":"IEC 62443-4-1","last_updated":"2023-10-15"} 
