ty Configuration Templates","url":"https://new.abb.com/control-systems/security","description":"ABB's templates for ICS security configurations."}]},{"id":"KA3","title":"Periodic Audit Procedures","description":"Defining and executing regular security audits to verify compliance with hardening guidelines and identify vulnerabilities.","related_links":[{"title":"ISA-62443-2-1 Audit Guidelines","url":" https://www.isa.org/products/ansi-isa-62443-2-1-2009-security-for-industrial-automation","description":"ISA's audit framework aligned with IEC 62443."},{"title":"Yokogawa Security Audit Checklist","url":"https://www.yokogawa.com/solutions/products-platforms/control-system/security/","description":"Yokogawa's checklist for ICS security audits."}]},{"id":"KA4","title":"Vendor-Specific Maintenance Guides","description":"Leveraging vendor-provided documentation for tailored maintenance instructions, ensuring compatibility and security.","related_links":[{"title":"Siemens Industrial Security Manual","url":" https://www.siemens.com/global/en/products/automation/industry-software/industrial-security.html","description":"Siemens' manual for ICS security maintenance."},{"title":"Emerson DeltaV Security Maintenance","url":"https://www.emerson.com/en-us/automation/deltav","description":"Emerson's guide for DeltaV system maintenance."}]}],"name":"Security hardening guidelines","description":"A process shall be employed to create product user documentation that includes guidelines for hardening the product when installing and maintaining the product. The guidelines shall include, but are not limited to, instructions, rationale and recommendations for the following: f) instructions and recommendations for periodic security maintenance activities;","details":{"risk_assessment_and_threat_modeling":{"why":"To identify potential vulnerabilities and threats that could affect the security of the product during its lifecycle.","methodologies":[{"name":"STRIDE","description":"A threat modeling methodology that identifies Spoofing, Tampering, Repudiation, Information Disclosure, Denial of Service, and Elevation of Privilege threats."},{"name":"ICS-specific threat models","description":"Custom threat models tailored for Industrial Control Systems to address unique operational and security challenges."}],"tools":[{"name":"Microsoft Threat Modeling Tool","purpose":"To create and analyze threat models using the STRIDE methodology."},{"name":"NIST 800-30 adapted for SCADA systems","purpose":"A risk assessment framework tailored for SCADA and ICS environments."}],"case_study":{"example":"A risk assessment was conducted for a Distributed Control System (DCS) in a power plant, identifying critical vulnerabilities in periodic maintenance activities and leading to the implementation of enhanced security controls."}},"audit_and_compliance_verification":{"why":"To ensure that the security hardening guidelines are effectively implemented and maintained.","audit_checklist":["Verify that periodic security maintenance activities are documented and followed.","Check for evidence of regular security updates and patches.","Ensure that hardening guidelines are reviewed and updated based on new threats."],"metrics":[{"kpi":"Percentage of scoped requirements implemented","target":"100%"},{"kpi":"Number of security incidents related to maintenance activities","target":"0"}],"compliance_procedure":"Documentation review and on-site audits to verify adherence to security hardening guidelines, with evidence recorded in compliance reports."},"training_and_competency_requirements":{"why":"To ensure that personnel responsible for security maintenance activities are adequately trained and competent.","training_programs":[{"name":"ISA/IEC 62443 certifications","description":"Certification programs covering the implementation and maintenance of ICS security standards."},{"name":"GICSP (Global Industrial Cyber Security Professional)","description":"A certification focused on securing industrial control systems."}],"competency_assessment":"Annual competency reviews to assess the knowledge and skills of personnel involved in security maintenance activities."},"tooling_and_automation_support":{"why":"To streamline and enhance the effectiveness of security maintenance activities.","tools":[{"name":"Ansible","purpose":"Automation tool for deploying security patches and configurations."},{"name":"Chef","purpose":"Configuration management tool to enforce security hardening guidelines."}],"automation_strategy":"Integration of security tools into DevSecOps pipelines to automate periodic maintenance tasks and ensure consistent application of hardening guidelines."},"handling_legacy_systems_and_constraints":{"why":"To address security challenges posed by legacy ICS components that cannot meet modern security standards.","strategies":[{"approach":"Network segmentation","description":"Isolate legacy systems to limit exposure to potential threats."},{"approach":"Compensating controls","description":"Implement additional security measures to mitigate risks associated with legacy systems."}],"example_policy":"A policy outlining the use of network segmentation and compensating controls for legacy PLCs that cannot be updated to meet current security standards."},"stakeholder_collaboration_and_governance":{"why":"To ensure effective collaboration and governance in implementing and maintaining security hardening guidelines.","governance_model":{"name":"RACI matrix","roles":[{"role":"Security Team","responsibility":"Define and update security hardening guidelines."},{"role":"Engineering Team","responsibility":"Implement and maintain hardening guidelines."},{"role":"Management","responsibility":"Oversee compliance and allocate resources."}]},"conflict_resolution":"A structured process for resolving conflicts between engineering and security priorities, including escalation to a governance committee if necessary."},"continuous_improvement_and_updates":{"why":"To adapt security hardening guidelines based on evolving threats and lessons learned.","update_process":[{"step":"Monitor threat intelligence","description":"Regularly review CISA alerts and other sources for new ICS vulnerabilities."},{"step":"Review audit findings","description":"Incorporate insights from audits and incidents into hardening guidelines."},{"step":"Update documentation","description":"Revise guidelines and communicate changes to all stakeholders."}],"lessons_learned":"Incorporating feedback from security incidents and audits to refine and improve security hardening guidelines."}},"standard_compliance":"IEC 62443-4-1","last_updated":"2023-10-15"} 
